==English==
===Etymology===
From Old English ''[[sceacga]]'', ''[[sceaga]]'' ([[coppice]]), related to Old Norse ''[[skegg]]'' ([[beard]])

===Noun===
'''shag'''

#a [[cormorant]], especially with a crest
#a type of carpet pile
#a [[swing]] [[dance]]
#the act of shagging, as in "have a good shag", as in [[sexual intercourse]]
#a social event, also typically a fund-raiser, that combines both a [[shower]] (also ''[[bridal shower]]'') and [[stag]] (local [[colloquialism]], ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thunder_Bay%2C_Ontario Thunder Bay, Ontario], [[Canada]]'')
#:Etymology: ''sh'' [from [[shower]]] + ''ag'' [from [[stag]]]

